    <h1>Comment Policy</h1>
    <p>We value respectful and constructive dialogue on our website. In order to maintain a positive and welcoming environment for all users, we have established the following guidelines:</p>
    
    <ul>
        <li><strong>No Negative Comments:</strong> Comments should be constructive and avoid negativity.</li>
        <li><strong>No Regional Discrimination:</strong> Please refrain from making discriminatory remarks based on geographical regions.</li>
        <li><strong>No Personal Attacks:</strong> Do not engage in personal attacks or insults against others.</li>
        <li><strong>No Defamation:</strong> Comments should not defame or damage the reputation of individuals or organizations.</li>
        <li><strong>No Disrespect towards Vietnam:</strong> It is prohibited to make derogatory remarks or defame the Socialist Republic of Vietnam.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We reserve the right to remove any comments that violate these guidelines, and repeated violations may result in the suspension or banning of commenting privileges.</p>

    <p>Thank you for your cooperation in maintaining a respectful and inclusive community.</p>
